Collection data : From alder and sphagnum litter in marshes; in beaver houses and muskrat nests; in beach debris; at UV light (
Chandler 1997
); also from leaf litter along streams. Habitat data from specimens indicates that this species is found in leaf litter along lake margins and in swamps/marshes. Several series have been taken from debris in beaver huts. This is a species of the Northeast and Midwest regions, with all collections but one being taken from March to November.
